{"parse":{"title":"Bipolar Spectrum Diagnostic Scale","pageid":30469534,"revid":856278275,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>The <b>Bipolar Spectrum Diagnostic Scale</b> (<b>BSDS</b>) is a <a href=\"/wiki/Psychiatry\" title=\"Psychiatry\">psychiatric</a> <a href=\"/wiki/Screening_(medicine)\" title=\"Screening (medicine)\">screening</a> <a href=\"/wiki/Rating_scale\" title=\"Rating scale\">rating scale</a> for <a href=\"/wiki/Bipolar_disorder\" title=\"Bipolar disorder\">bipolar disorder</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> It was developed by <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Ronald_Pies&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Ronald Pies (page does not exist)\">Ronald Pies</a>, and was later refined and tested by  <a href=\"/wiki/Nassir_Ghaemi\" title=\"Nassir Ghaemi\">S. Nassir Ghaemi</a> and colleagues. The BSDS arose from Pies's experience as a psychopharmacology consultant, where he was frequently called on to manage cases of \"<a href=\"/wiki/Treatment-resistant_depression\" title=\"Treatment-resistant depression\">treatment-resistant depression</a>\".\n</p><p>Their English version of the scale consists of 19 question items and two sections. It differs from most scales in that it does not list separate items, but rather presents a short paragraph talking about experiences that people with bipolar spectrum disorders often have. The person checks off which phrases or experiences fit them. \n</p><p>The scale was validated in its original version and demonstrated high diagnostic sensitivity, meaning that most people with confirmed bipolar diagnoses scored high on the BSDS.<sup id=\"cite_ref-pmid15708426_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-pmid15708426-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> The BSDS may do better than other scales at detecting types of bipolar disorder that do not involve a full manic episode, such as bipolar II or cyclothymic disorder. \n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Bipolar_Spectrum_Diagnostic_Scale&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Rating_scales_for_depression\" title=\"Rating scales for depression\">Rating scales for depression</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Bipolar_Spectrum_Diagnostic_Scale&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.psychiatrictimes.com/clinical-scales-bsds/bipolar-spectrum-diagnostic-scale-bsds\">\"Bipolar Spectrum Diagnostic Scale (BSDS)\"</a>. <i>Psychiatric Times</i>. UBM Medica, LLC. 11 April 2013.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=Psychiatric+Times&amp;rft.atitle=Bipolar+Spectrum+Diagnostic+Scale+%28BSDS%29&amp;rft.date=2013-04-11&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.psychiatrictimes.com%2Fclinical-scales-bsds%2Fbipolar-spectrum-diagnostic-scale-bsds&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABipolar+Spectrum+Diagnostic+Scale\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-pmid15708426-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-pmid15708426_2-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation journal\">Nassir Ghaemi, S; Miller, CJ; Berv, DA; Klugman, J; Rosenquist, KJ; Pies, RW (February 2005). \"Sensitivity and specificity of a new bipolar spectrum diagnostic scale\". <i>Journal of Affective Disorders</i>. <b>84</b> (2-3): 273\u20137. <a href=\"/wiki/Digital_object_identifier\" title=\"Digital object identifier\">doi</a>:<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//doi.org/10.1016/S0165-0327%2803%2900196-4\">10.1016/S0165-0327(03)00196-4</a>. <a href=\"/wiki/PubMed_Identifier\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"PubMed Identifier\">PMID</a>&#160;<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/15708426\">15708426</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Journal+of+Affective+Disorders&amp;rft.atitle=Sensitivity+and+specificity+of+a+new+bipolar+spectrum+diagnostic+scale&amp;rft.volume=84&amp;rft.issue=2-3&amp;rft.pages=273-7&amp;rft.date=2005-02&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.1016%2FS0165-0327%2803%2900196-4&amp;rft_id=info%3Apmid%2F15708426&amp;rft.aulast=Nassir+Ghaemi&amp;rft.aufirst=S&amp;rft.au=Miller%2C+CJ&amp;rft.au=Berv%2C+DA&amp;rft.au=Klugman%2C+J&amp;rft.au=Rosenquist%2C+KJ&amp;rft.au=Pies%2C+RW&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABipolar+Spectrum+Diagnostic+Scale\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<table class=\"metadata plainlinks stub\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"background:transparent\"><tbody><tr><td><a href=\"/wiki/File:Psi2.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Stub icon\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6c/Psi2.svg/30px-Psi2.svg.png\" width=\"30\" height=\"30\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6c/Psi2.svg/45px-Psi2.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6c/Psi2.svg/60px-Psi2.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"100\" data-file-height=\"100\" /></a></td><td><i